+      hyp("h25", "The strongest clinically coherent patterns in this cohort are treatment-biomarker interactions rather than nonspecific treatment main effects: matched targeted therapy and immune biomarkers show the largest positive `pfs_months` effects, while adverse disease-burden features show negative main effects.", "refined"),
+    ],
+    analyses: [
+      analysisRecord(["h25"], r.fitFullInteraction.osim_x_egfr, `Final synthesis model: osimertinib by egfr_mutation remained one of the largest positive interactions at ${round(r.fitFullInteraction.osim_x_egfr.beta, 3)} months (p=${formatP(r.fitFullInteraction.osim_x_egfr.p)}).`),
+      analysisRecord(["h25"], r.fitFullInteraction.soto_x_kras, `Final synthesis model: sotorasib by kras_g12c was ${round(r.fitFullInteraction.soto_x_kras.beta, 3)} months (p=${formatP(r.fitFullInteraction.soto_x_kras.p)}).`),
+      analysisRecord(["h25"], r.fitFullInteraction.pembro_x_stk11, `Final synthesis model: pembrolizumab by stk11_mutation was a negative interaction at ${round(r.fitFullInteraction.pembro_x_stk11.beta, 3)} months (p=${formatP(r.fitFullInteraction.pembro_x_stk11.p)}).`),
+      analysisRecord(["h25"], getCont("albumin_g_dl"), `Final synthesis model family: albumin_g_dl was a favorable disease-status marker with ${round(getCont("albumin_g_dl").beta, 3)} months per 1 g/dL (p=${formatP(getCont("albumin_g_dl").p)}).`),
+      analysisRecord(["h25"], getMain("liver_mets"), `Final synthesis model family: liver_mets was an adverse disease-burden marker with ${round(getMain("liver_mets").beta, 3)} months (p=${formatP(getMain("liver_mets").p)}).`),
+    ],
+  });
+
+  return out;
+}
+
+function buildSummary(r, iterations) {
+  const lines = [];
+  lines.push(`Dataset ${DATASET_ID}: ${r.n} NSCLC records; mean pfs_months ${round(r.pfsMean, 2)} (SD ${round(r.pfsSd, 2)}).`);
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("I ran 25 propose-test-refine iterations using linear models for pfs_months. Baseline-adjusted models controlled for age_years, sex_female, stage_iv, ecog_ps, has_brain_mets, albumin_g_dl, ldh_u_l, weight_loss_pct_6mo, crp_mg_l, nlr, smoking_status, and histology unless otherwise noted. P-values use large-sample normal approximations to the OLS coefficient tests.");
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("General disease-status effects were internally consistent. Higher albumin_g_dl was strongly favorable, while higher ldh_u_l, crp_mg_l, nlr, and weight_loss_pct_6mo were each associated with shorter PFS. Stage IV disease, brain metastases, liver metastases, bone metastases, pleural and pericardial effusions, adrenal metastases, and contralateral lung metastases were all adverse after adjustment.");
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("The clearest treatment-biomarker pattern was matched targeted therapy. The osimertinib by egfr_mutation interaction was strongly positive, the sotorasib by kras_g12c interaction was strongly positive, and the olaparib by brca2_mutation interaction was also positive. These persisted in a joint interaction model, supporting biomarker-specific treatment benefit rather than a nonspecific treatment main effect.");
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("Immunotherapy patterns were heterogeneous. Pembrolizumab benefit increased with tmb_high and with higher continuous pdl1_tps. In contrast, stk11_mutation and egfr_mutation attenuated pembrolizumab-associated PFS. The negative STK11 interaction remained in the joint interaction model. A three-way pembrolizumab by tmb_high by stk11_mutation term was small and not statistically significant, so the STK11 attenuation was not clearly confined to the TMB-high subgroup.");
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("Several explored refinements were weak or unsupported. Histology-squamous and current-smoking interactions with pembrolizumab were small compared with the molecular interactions. The osimertinib interaction scan identified egfr_mutation as the dominant effect, with metastatic-site interactions far smaller. Pembrolizumab scans ranked molecular features above most nonspecific clinical covariates.");
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("Overall conclusion: this cohort contains strong clinically coherent treatment-biomarker-outcome relationships. Matched targeted therapy markers and immune-response markers identify longer PFS on corresponding treatments, whereas inflammatory burden, metastatic burden, and STK11-associated immunotherapy resistance identify shorter PFS.");
+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("Selected effect estimates:");
+  for (const item of [
+    ["osimertinib x egfr_mutation", r.fitFullInteraction.osim_x_egfr],
+    ["sotorasib x kras_g12c", r.fitFullInteraction.soto_x_kras],
+    ["olaparib x brca2_mutation", r.fitFullInteraction.olap_x_brca2],
+    ["pembrolizumab x tmb_high", r.fitFullInteraction.pembro_x_tmb_high],
+    ["pembrolizumab x stk11_mutation", r.fitFullInteraction.pembro_x_stk11],
+  ]) {
+    lines.push(`- ${item[0]}: ${round(item[1].beta, 3)} months, p=${formatP(item[1].p)}`);
+  }
+  return lines.join("\n") + "\n";
+}
+
+function printDiagnostics(r) {
+  console.log(`Loaded ${r.n} rows; PFS mean ${round(r.pfsMean, 3)}, SD ${round(r.pfsSd, 3)}`);
+  console.log("Top adjusted binary main effects:");
+  for (const x of r.mainRanked.slice(0, 12)) console.log(x.v, round(x.adj.beta, 3), formatP(x.adj.p));
+  console.log("Top adjusted continuous main effects:");
+  for (const x of r.contRanked.slice(0, 12)) console.log(x.v, `per ${x.scale}`, round(x.adj.beta, 3), formatP(x.adj.p));
+  console.log("Treatment-biomarker interactions:");
+  for (const x of r.interactions) console.log(`${x.t} x ${x.b}`, round(x.res.interaction.beta, 3), formatP(x.res.interaction.p));
+  console.log("PDL1-pembro interaction", round(r.pdl1Pemb.interaction.beta, 3), formatP(r.pdl1Pemb.interaction.p));
+  for (const [t, scan] of Object.entries(r.treatmentInteractionScans)) {
+    console.log(`Top ${t} interaction scan:`);
+    for (const x of scan.slice(0, 8)) console.log(" ", x.b, round(x.res.interaction.beta, 3), formatP(x.res.interaction.p));
+  }
+  console.log("Treatment main effects:");
+  for (const x of r.treatmentMain) console.log(" ", x.v, "prev", round(x.prev, 3), "adj", round(x.adj.beta, 3), formatP(x.adj.p));
+  console.log("Wrote transcript.json and analysis_summary.txt");
+}
+
+analyze();

